  <summary date="2022-06-16T20:55:02Z" status="Introduced in House">Trade Adjustment Assistance Modernization Act of 2021

This bill reauthorizes through FY2028 and otherwise revises the Trade Adjustment Assistance Program, including by expanding program eligibility to additional workers, increasing relocation and job search allowances, establishing a child care allowance, and expanding eligibility for and increasing the maximum benefit of wage insurance. The bill also permanently extends the tax credit for health insurance costs and increases the percentage of such credit.</summary>
